## Relevant Defender Event IDs

Microsoft Defender Operational events commonly include:

| Event ID | General Description                               |
| -------: | ------------------------------------------------- |
|     1000 | Scan started                                      |
|     1001 | Scan completed                                    |
|     1006 | Malware or potentially unwanted software detected |
|     1007 | Action taken to protect the system                |
|     1008 | Action failed                                     |
|     1009 | Quarantine restoration activity                   |
|     1010 | Quarantine restoration failed                     |
|     1011 | Item deleted from quarantine                      |
|     1116 | Malware or potentially unwanted software detected |
|     1117 | Action taken to protect the system                |
|     1118 | Action failed                                     |
|     1119 | Critical error during action                      |
|     1121 | Controlled Folder Access blocked an action        |
|     2000 | Security intelligence updated                     |
|     2001 | Security intelligence update failed               |
|     5001 | Real-time protection disabled                     |
|     5004 | Defender configuration changed                    |
|     5007 | Defender configuration changed                    |

The exact events generated depend on the Windows and Defender build.

