## Detection Severity Guidance

| Pattern                                        | Suggested Context                        |
| ---------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Official harmless test detected and remediated | Informational or Low in test environment |
| Potentially unwanted application blocked       | Low or Medium                            |
| Malware detected and successfully quarantined  | Medium or High                           |
| Malware detected after execution               | High                                     |
| Remediation failed                             | High                                     |
| Threat repeatedly reappears                    | High                                     |
| Detection followed by Defender disablement     | Critical review                          |
| Same threat detected on multiple endpoints     | High or Critical                         |
| Ransomware or credential theft behavior        | Critical                                 |

Severity should reflect threat type, execution state, spread, and remediation result.

